# Anti-slop frontend (always)

Before any UI change, follow **`.cursor/skills/km0-anti-slop-design/SKILL.md`** and **`docs/design/anti-slop-doctrine.md`**.

## Auto-fail patterns

- Inter/Roboto/Open Sans as sole UI font
- Purple/indigo/violet brand gradients or gradient-clipped headlines
- Centered SaaS hero recipe (eyebrow pill + H1 + dual pill CTAs)
- Equal icon-tile feature cards / fake stat strips / glow-heavy decoration
- Default “AI nav” without a genre-specific alternative
- Zebra section rhythm (`nth-child` Paper/Snow alternation); continuous canvas + intentional bands only
- Generic map-pin / padded favicon / purple gradient pin instead of the Origin stamp mark system

## Required

- Distinct display + body pairing from `docs/brand-tokens.md`
- One anchor hue + restrained accent
- Biased (not fully centered) compositions where the page genre allows
- First viewport: brand, one headline, one support line, one CTA group, one dominant visual
- Phase-2 study when touching landing/chrome: `docs/design/reference-study-stirling-satisfecho-nous.md`

Tailwind is allowed as implementation detail. Tailwind’s **demo aesthetic** is not.
